    text: "Operation Ajax was a secret mission planned by the intelligence agencies of the United States and the United Kingdom. In 1953, the leader of Iran, Mohammad Mossadegh, decided to take control of the country's oil. Before this, British companies controlled the oil and made a lot of money. The British were very angry and asked the Americans for help. The CIA and the British secret service started a plan to remove Mossadegh from power. They spent a lot of money to pay people to protest in the streets and cause trouble. They also talked to the Iranian military and the Shah, who was the King of Iran. After a few days of chaos and fighting, the military arrested Mossadegh. The Shah returned to power and became a very strong leader with the help of the West. This operation was a success for the US and UK, but it made many Iranians very angry. They felt that other countries were interfering in their business. This event changed the history of the Middle East forever and led to many political problems in the future.",
