    text: "Operation Argo is one of the most famous and clever rescue missions in history. In 1979, during the Iran Hostage Crisis, protesters took over the American Embassy in Tehran. Most people were taken hostage, but six Americans managed to escape and hide in the home of the Canadian ambassador. They were trapped and very afraid of being caught. A CIA agent named Tony Mendez created a brilliant plan to save them. He pretended that the six Americans were a film crew from Canada. He said they were in Iran to find a location for a new science-fiction movie called Argo. He even created fake movie posters and advertisements in magazines. Mendez flew to Tehran with fake passports and met the group. He taught them how to act like movie makers. At the airport, they showed their fake documents to the guards. The plan worked perfectly, and they flew out of Iran safely. The world knew nothing about the truth for many years until it was finally made into a famous movie.",
