    text: "Operation Gunnerside was a vital mission to stop the Nazis from building an atomic bomb. During World War II, the Germans were using a factory in occupied Norway to produce 'heavy water,' which is needed for nuclear science. The British and the Norwegians knew they had to destroy the factory. A team of six Norwegian saboteurs jumped from a plane into the snowy mountains. They were expert skiers and survived the freezing cold for many days. They climbed down a very steep cliff, crossed a frozen river, and climbed up to the factory. They secretly entered the building and placed explosives on the heavy water machines. The explosion destroyed the factory’s production. The men then skied hundreds of kilometers across the mountains to escape into neutral Sweden. They fired no shots during the mission. This spectacular operation was a huge success and it delayed the German nuclear program, helping to win the war. It is remembered as one of the best examples of sabotage in history.",
