    text: "Operation Isotope was a daring rescue of a hijacked airplane. In May 1972, four terrorists from the Black September group hijacked a Sabena flight traveling from Belgium to Israel. They forced the pilot to land at Lod Airport near Tel Aviv. They took 100 people hostage and demanded the release of 317 prisoners. They threatened to blow up the plane with everyone inside. The Israeli government pretended to negotiate with the hijackers. They told the terrorists that the plane needed repairs before it could fly again. A group of sixteen commandos, including future leaders Ehud Barak and Benjamin Netanyahu, dressed up as airplane mechanics in white overalls. They walked toward the plane carrying their tools, but their weapons were hidden under their clothes. They suddenly stormed the plane through the doors. In less than two minutes, they killed the two male terrorists and captured the two female terrorists. All the passengers were saved, although one woman was accidentally killed in the crossfire. This fast and clever operation was a major success for Israel’s special forces.",
