    text: "Operation Jaque was a brilliant and peaceful rescue mission in Colombia. For many years, a rebel group called the FARC held many people as hostages in the thick jungle. This included the famous politician Ingrid Betancourt and three American workers. The Colombian military spent a long time planning a trick to save them. They created a fake humanitarian group. They used helicopters and painted them white to look like they belonged to an international aid organization. The soldiers dressed in civilian clothes and acted like doctors and reporters. They met with the rebels and told them they needed to move the hostages to a different camp. The rebels believed the trick and let the hostages get onto the helicopter. Once the helicopter was high in the air, the soldiers told the hostages, 'We are the national army. You are free.' The rebels on the ground had no idea what happened until it was too late. Nobody was shot during this perfect and clever mission. It was a massive victory for Colombia.",
