    text: "Operation Neptune Spear was the top-secret mission to find and kill Osama bin Laden. For ten years after the 9/11 attacks, the United States searched for the leader of Al-Qaeda. Finally, intelligence found that he was hiding in a large, private house in Abbottabad, Pakistan. President Barack Obama ordered a secret night raid. A team of US Navy SEALs flew from Afghanistan in special helicopters that were designed to be quiet and invisible to radar. They landed inside the walls of the house and began a fast gunfight with the guards. They found bin Laden on the third floor and killed him. They also took many computers and documents to learn more about his group. The entire mission lasted only about 40 minutes. One helicopter crashed during the landing, but no Americans were killed. They blew up the broken helicopter and flew away before the Pakistani military could arrive. This operation was one of the most important events in the history of the war on terror.",
