    text: "Operation Nimrod was a spectacular hostage rescue that happened live on television. in 1980, six armed men took over the Iranian Embassy in London. They took 26 people hostage and demanded that Iran release prisoners. The siege lasted for six days while the police tried to talk to the gunmen. On the sixth day, the gunmen killed one of the hostages and threw his body out of the front door. The British government decided to send the SAS, a group of elite soldiers. Millions of people watched on the news as the black-clothed soldiers climbed down ropes from the roof and used explosives to enter the windows. The soldiers moved very fast through the smoke and fire. They killed five of the six terrorists and saved almost all the hostages. Only one hostage was killed by the gunmen during the attack. This mission made the SAS very famous around the world and showed that Britain was very strong against terrorism.",
